  "texts": [
    "The default cutoff radius for HamNet and GIN was set to 5 angstroms, while the maximum number of neighbors for nodes (excluding self, as self-loops are allowed) was limited to 17.",
    "When dealing with edges in the graph, we first computed the distance matrix between nodes, then selected edges based on the cutoff radius as a threshold, limiting the number of neighbors to within the default value of 17.",
    "For DenseGNN, we employed the KNN edge selection method, with the parameter k set to 12 for optimal performance.",
    "The KNN method relies on the number of neighbors k, but edge distances may vary with changes in crystal density.",
    "Subsequently, we applied a Gaussian kernel function to extend edge lengths and used them as the edge features of our model's graph."
  ],
